🔍 Advanced Log Analysis

🎯 Objective
Perform log correlation, detect anomalies, and enrich log data using SIEM tools to identify suspicious activities.

🛠️ Tools Used
Wazuh (SIEM platform)
Linux system logs (sshd, PAM)
GeoIP (built-in Wazuh enrichment)

📊 Log Correlation
Multiple failed SSH login attempts were generated and analyzed. The logs showed repeated authentication failures from the same source IP, indicating a brute-force attack.

📌 Correlated Log Data
Timestamp	Event ID	Source IP	Destination IP	Notes
2026-04-03 11:46:46	5712	127.0.0.1	localhost	SSH brute force attempt detected
2026-04-03 11:46:42	5710	127.0.0.1	localhost	Multiple failed login attempts

🚨 Anomaly Detection
An anomaly was identified based on:
High frequency of failed login attempts within a short time
Elevated rule level (level 10 alerts in Wazuh)

🔧 Detection Rule (Conceptual - Elastic Equivalent)
IF failed_logins > threshold (5 attempts in 1 minute)
THEN trigger alert (possible brute-force attack)

🌍 Log Enrichment (GeoIP)
The source IP address was analyzed using GeoIP enrichment. Since the activity originated from 127.0.0.1 (localhost), it indicates internal testing. In real-world scenarios, external IPs would be enriched with geographic location data to assess risk.
